  <!-- FILE ATTACHMENTS -->
  <section id="file-attachments">
    <h2>File Attachments</h2>
    <p>Users can attach files to any message. Files are read into memory using <code>FileReader</code> and sent as multi-part content to the API.</p>

    <h3>Supported file types</h3>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <tr><th>Type</th><th>Sent as</th><th>Icon</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Images (jpg, png, gif, webp)</td><td>base64 data URL</td><td>🖼️</td><td>Sent as <code>image_url</code> content part; supports vision models</td></tr>
        <tr><td>PDF</td><td>base64 data URL</td><td>📄</td><td>Sent as <code>document</code> content part where supported</td></tr>
        <tr><td>CSV</td><td>plain text</td><td>📊</td><td>Included as text block in the message</td></tr>
        <tr><td>JSON</td><td>plain text</td><td>📋</td><td>Included as text block in the message</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Text files (.txt, .md, .js, etc.)</td><td>plain text</td><td>📝</td><td>Included as text block</td></tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3>Attachment lifecycle</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>User clicks the 📎 button or drags a file into the input area, or pastes an image from the clipboard.</li>
      <li><code>attachFiles(fileList)</code> reads each file with <code>readFile()</code> and pushes to <code>S.files</code>.</li>
      <li>Chips appear in the <code>#attached-files</code> bar above the input showing filename, type icon, and size.</li>
      <li>On send, <code>buildApiMsgs()</code> converts <code>S.files</code> entries into the correct content part format for the active provider.</li>
      <li><code>S.files</code> is cleared after the message is sent.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Clipboard paste</h3>
    <p>A global <code>paste</code> event listener intercepts clipboard images and calls <code>attachFiles()</code> automatically. Text pastes are not intercepted and go into the textarea normally.</p>

    <h3>Storage note</h3>
    <p>File contents are stored in messages as base64 strings (<code>m.files[].data</code>) in IndexedDB. Images and PDFs can be large — the message save function strips image data from persisted messages to keep IndexedDB size manageable, keeping only <code>{name, type}</code> metadata.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- FILE GENERATORS -->
  <section id="file-generators">
    <h2>File Generation</h2>
    <p>When the AI returns a fenced block with a format tag (<code>pdf-content</code>, <code>docx-content</code>, <code>pptx-content</code>), the renderer shows a download button instead of a code preview. Clicking it calls the appropriate generator.</p>

    <h3>Lazy loading</h3>
    <p>All generator libraries are loaded on first use via <code>loadScript(src)</code>, which injects a <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tag and returns a Promise. The browser caches them after the first load.</p>

    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <tr><th>Format</th><th>Function</th><th>Library</th><th>CDN URL</th></tr>
        <tr><td>PDF</td><td><code>generatePDF(jsonStr, filename)</code></td><td>jsPDF 2.5.1</td><td>cdnjs.cloudflare.com</td></tr>
        <tr><td>DOCX</td><td><code>generateDOCX(jsonStr, filename)</code></td><td>docx.js</td><td>cdnjs.cloudflare.com</td></tr>
        <tr><td>PPTX</td><td><code>generatePPTX(jsonStr, filename)</code></td><td>pptxgenjs</td><td>cdnjs.cloudflare.com</td></tr>
        <tr><td>CSS</td><td><code>generateCSS(cssStr, filename)</code></td><td>None (plain Blob)</td><td>—</td></tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3>JSON parsing</h3>
    <p><code>parseModelJSON(raw)</code> defensively extracts the JSON object from the model's raw output. It strips markdown fences the model may have added inside the block, then finds the first <code>{</code> and last <code>}</code> to extract the JSON regardless of any surrounding prose.</p>

    <h3>PDF generation details</h3>
    <p>The PDF generator uses jsPDF in millimetre mode. Page setup (size, orientation, margins) can be set in <code>_vePageSetup</code> from the visual editor. It renders title, optional author, a decorative rule, section headings, body paragraphs, and bullet lists. Page overflow is handled by <code>checkPage(need)</code> which adds a new page when less than <code>need</code> mm remain.</p>

    <h3>PPTX generation details</h3>
    <p>The PPTX generator uses pptxgenjs. Each slide in the JSON array becomes a slide object with title, optional body text, and optional bullet points. Speaker notes are added to the slide's notes pane. A consistent theme (background, accent colour, font family) is applied from the visual editor's current state if available.</p>

    <h3>DOCX generation details</h3>
    <p>The DOCX generator uses docx.js. Section headings become <code>Heading1</code> paragraphs. Body text becomes normal paragraphs. Bullet lists become list items. The output is a valid <code>.docx</code> file downloadable by the browser via an object URL.</p>
  </section>

