  <!-- COST DETAIL -->
  <section id="cost-detail">
    <h2>Cost Calculation</h2>
    <p>Cost tracking uses per-token pricing from the model object. All costs are in USD.</p>

    <h3>Formula</h3>
    <pre>cost = iTok × model.pricing.prompt + oTok × model.pricing.completion</pre>
    <p>Pricing values are stored as USD per token (not per million). OpenRouter's <code>/models</code> endpoint returns them in this format directly.</p>

    <h3>Free providers</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Gemini (AI Studio key):</strong> All models show "Free*" unless <code>S.cfg.geminiTrackCost</code> is true. The free tier covers generous daily quotas — cost tracking is disabled by default since users won't be billed.</li>
      <li><strong>Local provider:</strong> Always shows "Local" — no API billing.</li>
      <li><strong>Local model (WebGPU):</strong> No cost shown — inference runs on the user's GPU.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Pre-send estimate</h3>
    <p><code>updateEst()</code> fires on every keystroke in the input textarea. It estimates token count as <code>Math.ceil(text.length / 4)</code> (4 chars ≈ 1 token) and shows the estimated input cost below the input box.</p>

    <h3>Budget enforcement</h3>
    <p>If <code>S.budget > 0</code> and <code>S.totalCost >= S.budget</code>, <code>sendMessage()</code> blocks the send and shows a warning toast. The budget bar in the topbar fills proportionally and changes colour at 60% (amber) and 90% (red).</p>
  </section>

  <!-- SECURITY -->
  <section id="security">
    <h2>Security Model</h2>

    <h3>API key storage tiers</h3>
    <p>Keys are stored using a preference-ordered fallback:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Credential Management API</strong> — Browser-managed, persists across sessions, not accessible via JavaScript after storage. Best security. Shown as "🔒 Secure" in the topbar.</li>
      <li><strong>SessionStorage</strong> — In-memory per tab, cleared on close. Used when Credential API is unavailable (Firefox, some Safari configs). Shown as "⚠ Session only".</li>
      <li><strong>None</strong> — Key not stored. User must re-enter on next visit.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>Keys are <strong>never</strong> written to <code>localStorage</code>, <code>S</code> serialisation, Drive backup, or export files.</p>

    <h3>Content sanitisation</h3>
    <p>All AI-generated HTML is passed through DOMPurify before being inserted into the DOM via <code>innerHTML</code>. This prevents XSS from malicious model outputs.</p>

    <h3>Artifact sandbox</h3>
    <p>Artifacts are rendered in <code>&lt;iframe&gt;</code> elements with a <code>sandbox</code> attribute. Scripts inside the artifact cannot access the parent page's DOM or <code>window</code> object.</p>

    <h3>Google OAuth scope minimisation</h3>
    <p>Only <code>drive.file</code> is requested — the narrowest Drive scope. Atlas cannot read any existing Drive files; only the single <code>atlas-chat-history.json</code> file it creates.</p>

    <h3>No telemetry</h3>
    <p>Atlas makes no analytics calls, no error reporting calls, and no calls to any Atlas-controlled server. All network traffic goes exclusively to the AI provider API you configure and to Google's APIs if signed in.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ADDING A PROVIDER -->
  <section id="adding-provider">
    <h2>How To: Add a Provider</h2>
    <p>To add a new cloud AI provider:</p>

    <ol>
      <li><strong>Add a key field to S</strong> — e.g. <code>S.mistralKey = ''</code></li>
      <li><strong>Add a provider ID string</strong> — e.g. <code>'mistral'</code> as a valid value for <code>S.provider</code></li>
      <li><strong>Update the active key resolver</strong> in <code>sendMessage()</code>:</li>
    </ol>
    <pre>const activeKey =
  S.provider === <span class="str">'mistral'</span> ? S.mistralKey :
  <span class="com">// ... existing providers</span></pre>

    <ol start="4">
      <li><strong>Add a model list fetcher</strong> in <code>reloadModels()</code> — handle the <code>'mistral'</code> case, fetch from the provider's models endpoint, normalise to <code>{id, name, context_length, pricing}</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>Add streaming handler</strong> in <code>callApi()</code> — if the provider uses OpenAI-compatible SSE, only the base URL and auth header need changing. If it uses a different format (like Gemini), add a parallel function.</li>
      <li><strong>Add key UI</strong> — add a tab button in the API Keys section of <code>index.html</code> and handle it in <code>aksSwitch()</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>Add to KeyStore</strong> — call <code>KeyStore.saveKey('mistral', val)</code> in <code>aksSaveKey()</code> and <code>KeyStore.loadKey('mistral')</code> in <code>initSecureStorage()</code>.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <!-- ADDING A SKILL -->
  <section id="adding-skill">
    <h2>How To: Add a Built-in Skill</h2>
    <p>Built-in skills are defined in the <code>BUILTIN_SKILLS</code> array near the top of atlas.js.</p>

    <pre>BUILTIN_SKILLS.push({
  id:     <span class="str">'legal'</span>,
  icon:   <span class="str">'⚖️'</span>,
  name:   <span class="str">'Legal Writing'</span>,
  desc:   <span class="str">'Precise, citation-ready legal documents and analysis'</span>,
  prompt: <span class="str">`Your system prompt here. Be specific about tone,
structure, and what the model should avoid or prioritise.`</span>
});</pre>

    <p>To add the skill to the intent auto-detector, add a mapping in the <code>INTENT_MAP</code> object:</p>
    <pre>INTENT_MAP[<span class="str">'legal'</span>] = [
  <span class="str">'contract'</span>, <span class="str">'lawsuit'</span>, <span class="str">'clause'</span>, <span class="str">'legal'</span>, <span class="str">'liability'</span>, <span class="str">'statute'</span>
];</pre>
    <p>Keywords are matched case-insensitively against the user's input. First match wins.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ADDING A TOOL -->
  <section id="adding-tool">
    <h2>How To: Add a Tool</h2>
    <p>Tools are defined in <code>initToolDefinitions()</code> and executed in the tool call handler inside <code>sendMessage()</code>.</p>

    <h4>1. Define the schema</h4>
    <pre>S.toolDefinitions.push({
  type: <span class="str">'function'</span>,
  function: {
    name:        <span class="str">'get_weather'</span>,
    description: <span class="str">'Get current weather for a city'</span>,
    parameters: {
      type: <span class="str">'object'</span>,
      properties: {
        city: { type: <span class="str">'string'</span>, description: <span class="str">'City name'</span> }
      },
      required: [<span class="str">'city'</span>]
    }
  }
});</pre>

    <h4>2. Handle execution</h4>
    <p>In the tool call handler block inside <code>sendMessage()</code>, add a case:</p>
    <pre><span class="kw">if</span> (name === <span class="str">'get_weather'</span>) {
  const data = <span class="kw">await</span> fetch(<span class="str">`https://wttr.in/${args.city}?format=j1`</span>);
  result = { weather: (await data.json()).current_condition[<span class="num">0</span>] };
}</pre>

    <div class="callout warn">
      <span class="callout-icon">⚠️</span>
      <div class="callout-body">Tool schemas are sent with every API request when <code>S.toolDefinitions</code> is non-empty. Keep the total schema size small — each tool adds to the system prompt token count and therefore to cost.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

